TRAPPING RAIN WATER
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Given n non-negative integers representing an elevation map where the width of each bar is 1,
compute how much water it can trap after raining.


EXAMPLE 1
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Input:  height = [0,1,0,2,1,0,1,3,2,1,2,1]
Output: 6

Explanation:
Total trapped rain water = 6 units.


EXAMPLE 2
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Input:  height = [4,2,0,3,2,5]
Output: 9


CONSTRAINTS
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
n == height.length
1 <= n <= 2 * 10⁴
0 <= height[i] <= 10⁵


OPTIMIZED APPROACH
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
1. Find the tallest bar (peak index).
2. Traverse from LEFT → peak
   • Maintain leftmax
   • Water += leftmax − height[i] when height smaller
3. Traverse from RIGHT → peak
   • Maintain rightmax
   • Water += rightmax − height[i]
4. Return total water.


TIME COMPLEXITY : O(n)  
SPACE COMPLEXITY : O(1)


CODE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

class Solution {
public:
    int trap(vector<int>& height) {
        int n = height.size();
        int index;
        int water = 0;

        int leftmax = height[0];
        int rightmax = height[n-1];
        int max = height[0];

        // find tallest building
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
        {
            if(height[i] > max)
            {
                max = height[i];
                index = i;
            }
        }

        // left → tallest
        for(int i=0;i<index;i++)
        {
            if(height[i] > leftmax)
                leftmax = height[i];
            else
                water += (leftmax - height[i]);
        }

        // right → tallest
        for(int i=n-1;i>index;i--)
        {
            if(height[i] > rightmax)
                rightmax = height[i];
            else
                water += (rightmax - height[i]);
        }

        return water;
    }
};
